TITLE: Two Americans and five Russians charged with running a smuggling network to obtain military technology and ammunition for Russia
SUMMARY: Two American citizens and five Russian nationals were charged with smuggling sensitive military technology and ammunition to benefit the Kremlin.

TITLE: Biden signs bill to protect same-sex and interracial marriages
SUMMARY: The Respect for Marriage Act does not guarantee the right to marry, but it specifies that states must recognize same-sex marriages across state lines.

TITLE: CFTC piles on with new charges against Bankman-Fried, FTX and Alameda
SUMMARY: The Commodity Futures Trading Commission alleged that FTX commingled customer funds and that ex-CEO Sam Bankman-Fried violated the Commodities Exchange Act.

TITLE: Sen. Warren presses Defense Secretary about ex-Google CEO Schmidt's potential conflicts when he advised Pentagon on AI
SUMMARY: Elizabeth Warren pressed Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin about ex-Google CEO Eric Schmidt's time on advisory panels connected to an industry he was investing in.

TITLE: Sam Bankman-Fried diverted FTX customer funds to donate to political campaigns, authorities charge
SUMMARY: FTX founder Sam Bankman-Fried is accused of using his crypto hedge fund Alameda Research as a "personal piggy bank" to make illegal political contributions.

TITLE: Congress considers crypto consumer protection bill that Sam Bankman-Fried backed before FTX collapse
SUMMARY: The Digital Commodities Consumer Protection Act would have protected customers from a failure like that of crypto giant FTX, lawmakers say.

TITLE: Sam Bankman-Fried criminal charges unsealed: Conspiracy to defraud the U.S., wire fraud, securities fraud, and money laundering
SUMMARY: Federal prosecutors accuse FTX co-founder Sam Bankman-Fried of widespread fraud and violating campaign finance laws, a new indictment says.

TITLE: Biden celebrates easing inflation numbers, defends his economic policies
SUMMARY: The core consumer price index, which excludes food and energy costs and is viewed as a primary indicator of inflation by economists, rose only 0.2% in November.

TITLE: Former FTX CEO Sam Bankman-Fried refuses to testify before Senate, committee says
SUMMARY: FTX CEO Sam Bankman-Fried refused to testify at a Wednesday hearing in front of the Senate Banking Committee.

TITLE: DOJ special counsel in Trump probe subpoenas Georgia secretary of state
SUMMARY: Donald Trump faces two criminal probes led by Jack Smith, the Justice Department's special counsel, one of which relates to his election loss to Joe Biden.

TITLE: New FTX CEO to tell Congress about bankrupt crypto firm's 'spending binge,' loans to insiders
SUMMARY: FTX CEO John J. Ray III plans to testify before the House Financial Services Committee on Tuesday.

TITLE: Supreme Court takes second case challenging Biden student loan relief
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court will decide the legality of Joe Biden's student loan relief program, which could forgive $400 billion of debt.

TITLE: Judge dismisses Trump's case challenging Mar-a-Lago document seizure after appeals court ends special master review
SUMMARY: Judge Aileen Cannon's order came after Trump declined to fight an appellate ruling that stopped a special master from reviewing the Mar-a-Lago materials.

TITLE: Meet the megadonors backing the Trump super PAC as some top donors opt out of supporting 2024 candidacy
SUMMARY: A small group of megadonors are backing a super PAC supporting Donald Trump's 2024 candidacy as other business leaders distance themselves.

TITLE: Sen. Sinema's switch to Independent will not impact Democrats' control of the chamber, representatives say
SUMMARY: Many members of Congress have said Sinema's switch likely won't impact the Democrats' narrow control of the U.S. Senate.

TITLE: Supreme Court takes Coinbase appeal over crypto lawsuits
SUMMARY: The eventual Supreme Court ruling in the appeal by crypto exchange Coinbase could resolve a split between appeals court on a question involving arbitration.

TITLE: Judge does not hold Trump office in contempt of court despite DOJ request
SUMMARY: Donald Trump, who is again running for the White House, is under criminal investigation for the removal of government documents when his presidency ended.

TITLE: Arizona Sen. Kyrsten Sinema leaves Democratic Party to become independent
SUMMARY: Sinema said in a tweet she was declaring her "independence from the broken partisan system in Washington and formally registering as an Arizona Independent."

TITLE: McCarthy's struggle to lock down House speaker roils GOP caucus, delays key committee assignments
SUMMARY: GOP leader Kevin McCarthy's struggle to win 218 votes to be House speaker threatens to delay Republicans' plans to hit the ground running in the new majority.

TITLE: DOJ asks judge to hold Trump in contempt over classified documents subpoena, reports say
SUMMARY: A raid of the Mar-a-Lago home of Donald Trump found classified documents and thousands of other government records removed from the White House.

TITLE: SEC issues new guidance requiring companies to disclose cryptocurrency risks
SUMMARY: Under the new SEC guidance, companies will have to include crypto asset holdings as well as their risk exposure to the FTX bankruptcy in their public filings.

TITLE: House passes massive $858 billion defense bill that would scrap military Covid vaccine mandate, teeing up Senate vote
SUMMARY: The defense bill contains a requirement that the Pentagon drop its Covid vaccine mandate for active duty service members within 30 days of its enactment.

TITLE: U.S. lawmakers press federal banking regulators on the industryâ€™s exposure to crypto after Alameda stake in bank comes to light
SUMMARY: Sens. Elizabeth Warren and Tina Smith sent letters to three federal financial regulators seeking information into possible ties between banks and crypto firms.

TITLE: Former FTX CEO Sam Bankman-Fried hit with campaign finance complaint over GOP 'dark' money
SUMMARY: CREW's campaign finance complaint against Sam Bankman-Fried comes nearly a month after his FTX crypto exchange filed for bankruptcy protection.

TITLE: House passes landmark bill to protect same-sex marriages, sending it to Biden's desk
SUMMARY: The U.S. House of Representatives passed a landmark bill Thursday enshrining federal protections for same-sex and interracial marriage.

TITLE: FDA authorizes Covid omicron vaccines for children as young as 6 months old
SUMMARY: The FDA's decision to authorize the shots for the youngest kids comes as Covid infections and hospitalizations are increasing nationally.

TITLE: Biden administration brings WNBA star Brittney Griner home after she was imprisoned for 10 months in Russia
SUMMARY: Griner was arrested 10 months ago for possession of two vape cartridges containing hashish oil while traveling through an airport near Moscow.

TITLE: House Financial Services Chair Waters doesn't plan to subpoena Sam Bankman-Fried to testify at hearing on FTX collapse
SUMMARY: House Financial Services Chair Maxine Waters tells members there are no current plans to subpoena FTX founder Sam Bankman-Fried for his testimony.

TITLE: Trump search team finds at least 2 classified documents outside of Mar-a-Lago
SUMMARY: Donald Trump is under criminal investigation by the Department of Justice for his removal of government documents from the White House when he left office.

TITLE: Cryptocurrency firms need to 'come into compliance' with existing rules, SEC Chair Gary Gensler says
SUMMARY: SEC Chair Gary Gensler says rules are in place to regulate cryptocurrency exchanges, but companies must comply with existing rules.
